Sentencas: CeO2 existed in the form of quantum dots were used in fuel cell electrolytes for the first time after being compounded with semiconductor TiO2.
Titulo: Applications of quantum dot membrane electrolytes in LT-SOFCs

Sentencas: The TiO2 @xCeO2 (x = 1,2,3) was evaluated as the membrane electrolyte for the semiconductor-ions membrane electrolyte fuel cells using H2 as fuels.
Titulo: Applications of quantum dot membrane electrolytes in LT-SOFCs

Sentencas: The maximum power density of the TiO2 @ 2CeO2 quantum dot electrolyte at 550 degrees C reaches 839 mW cm-2, and the ion conductivity reaches 0.11 S cm-1, which is higher than the physically mixed TiO2/CeO2 composite under the same operating environment.
Titulo: Applications of quantum dot membrane electrolytes in LT-SOFCs

Sentencas: The energy band structure and rectification characteristics test show that the cell based on TiO2/CeO2 electrolyte membrane has a physical junction effect, which can prevent electrons from passing through the interior and effectively avoid short-circuit problems.
Titulo: Applications of quantum dot membrane electrolytes in LT-SOFCs

Sentencas: This study shows that the TiO2 @xCeO2 (x = 1,2,3) composite in quantum dots form is a promising electrolyte that can promote the development of low-temperature solid oxide fuel cell.
Titulo: Applications of quantum dot membrane electrolytes in LT-SOFCs
